-- China Drafting Legislation to Compensate Wrongly Imprisoned, Xinhua Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-04-27T00:03:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-27/china-drafting-legislation-to-compensate-wrongly-imprisoned-xinhua-says.html

          
          
             Draft amendments to Chinese law 
would require the government to compensate those imprisoned on 
charges they are later exonerated of, the official Xinhua News 
Agency reported.  
 Individuals whose cases are dropped by prosecutors after 
“excessive” long periods of detention should also be 
compensated by the government, Xinhua reported. The amendments 
were submitted for discussion yesterday to the National 
People’s Congress Standing Committee, Xinhua reported.   
